### Government

The county's governmental structure, as one might expect, is traditionally organized in strict adherence to Virginia Law. It is presided over by a [Board of Supervisors](/Board_of_Supervisors), whose members are elected to four-year terms by the voters residing within each of the county's five distinct districts. This Board, in its infinite wisdom, then appoints a County Administrator to serve as the chief administrative officer, tasked with the unenviable job of actually running things. The current individual holding this rather pivotal position is Neil Morgan.

